  "description": {
   "value": "<p><em>Rod - Legendary (Requires Attunement)</em></p><p><strong>Buff</strong></p><ul><li><p>The rod functions as a +3 magic Mace.</p></li><li><p><strong>Drain Life: </strong>When you hit with a melee attack using the rod, you can force the target to make a [[/save CON 17]]{DC 17 Constitution saving throw}. On a failure, it takes an extra 4d6 Necrotic damage and you regain Hit Points equal to half that damage. Once used, this property can't be used again until the next dawn.</p></li><li><p><strong>Paralyze: </strong>When you hit with a melee attack using the rod, you can force the target to make a [[/save CON 17]]{DC 17 Constitution saving throw}. On a failure, it has the &amp;reference[Paralyzed apply=false] condition for 1 minute (repeat the save at the end of each of its turns). Once used, this property can't be used again until the next dawn.</p></li><li><p><strong>Terrify: </strong>As an Action, you can force each creature you can see within 30 feet to make a [[/save WIS 17]]{DC 17 Wisdom saving throw}. On a failure, the target has the &amp;reference[Frightened apply=false] condition for 1 minute (repeat the save at the end of each of its turns). Once used, this property can't be used again until the next dawn.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Bonus Action</strong></p><ul><li><p>You can press one of six buttons on the haft; the chosen effect lasts until you press a different button or press the same button again.</p></li></ul><details><summary>Button Effects</summary><p><strong>Button 1.</strong> A fiery blade sprouts from the tip, functioning as a magic Longsword or Shortsword (your choice) that sheds Bright Light in a 40-foot radius, Dim Light for another 40 feet, and deals an extra 2d6 Fire damage on a hit.</p><p><strong>Button 2.</strong> The rod becomes a magic Battleaxe that grants a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls.</p><p><strong>Button 3.</strong> The rod becomes a magic Spear with a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls.</p><p><strong>Button 4.</strong> The rod becomes a 50-foot climbing pole with anchoring spike, hooks, and ladder rungs that can support up to 4,000 pounds.</p><p><strong>Button 5.</strong> The rod becomes a handheld battering ram, granting a +10 bonus to Strength (Athletics) checks made to break barriers.</p><p><strong>Button 6.</strong> The rod indicates magnetic north (if any) and reveals your approximate height above or depth below ground.</p><ul><li></li></ul></details><section class=\"secret\" id=\"foundry-secret-1\"><p>An activity has been added for each usable button that implements the attack with the relevant bonuses.</p><p>The properties are also implemented as activities and track their own uses per dawn.</p><p>When using Button 5, you can manually add a +10 bonus in the Situational Bonus field when making the check.</p></section>",
